tle" colspan="2">BLIZZARD CERAMICA LLP</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td colspan="2">SUBJECT : Table of contents</td>                    <td>Edition No. : 01</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td colspan="2">Standard : ISO 9001 : 2015</td>                    <td>Rev. No. & Date : 01 / 01.08.2024</td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td colspan="3">Page No. : 51 of 79</td>                </tr>            </table>            <tr>                <td class="left-col" style="margin-left:10%">(C) “INVALID &nbsp; COPY”:</td>                <td class="right-col">                    Whenever revision takes place, the obsolete                    documented information shall be withdrawn                    and marked with “INVALID &nbsp; COPY” stamp in blue color.                </td>            </tr>            <br />            <br />            <tr>                <td class="left-col" style="margin-left:10%">(D) “REFERENCE &nbsp; COPY”:</td>                <td class="right-col">                    Any documented information issued to in-                    house or outside only for                    reference shal be marked with                    “REFERENCE &nbsp; COPY” stamp in blue color.                </td>            </tr>            <br />            <p> PARTNER &nbsp; keeps all stamps used in the system in safe custody to avoid unauthorized use. </p>            <br />            <br />            <p>CONTROL &nbsp; OF &nbsp; DOCUMENTS: </p>            <p>                The documented Information are established and maintained to demonstrate the evidence of conformance to the specified requirements and effective operation of the quality management system. Pertinent retain documented Information from suppliers have been identified.            </p>            <p>All documented Information are indexed and filed so that those can be easily retrieved whenever required. </p>            <p>All documented Information are retained and stored in such a way that they are readily retrievable in facilities that provide a suitable environment to prevent damage, deterioration and loss. </p>            <p>The retention time of the documented Information has been defined and maintained up to the defined retention time. After completion of retention time, all retain documented Information are disposed by suitable means.</p>            <table class="header-table">                <tr>                    <td style="width:35%; height:5vh;"></td>                    <td style="width:35%; height:5vh;"></td>                    <td rowspan="2"></td>                </tr>                <tr>                    <td class="text-center">Prepared By </td>                    <td class="text-center">Approved By</td>                </tr>            </table>        </div>    </div>    <script>        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", () => {            document.getElementById("downloadPdf").addEventListener("click", () => {                const { jsPDF } = window.jspdf;                const pdf = new jsPDF("p", "mm", "a4");                // Get elements to hide                const btn = document.getElementById("downloadPdf");                const logo = document.getElementById("top-logo");                // Temporarily hide elements                if (btn) btn.style.display = "none";                if (logo) logo.style.display = "none";                html2canvas(document.getElementById("pdf-content")).then(canvas => {                    const imgData = canvas.toDataURL("image/png");                    const imgWidth = 190; // A4 width in mm                    const imgHeight = (canvas.height * imgWidth) / canvas.width;                    pdf.addImage(imgData, "PNG", 10, 10, imgWidth, imgHeight);                    pdf.save("QM_P51.pdf");                    // Restore elements after PDF is generated                    if (btn) btn.style.display = "block";                    if (logo) logo.style.display = "block";                });            });        });    </script></body></html>